  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2009-05-13",
    "date": "2009-06-05T15:43:14Z",
    "text": "21st Century Skills Incentive Fund Act - Authorizes the Secretary of Education to award matching grants to states to establish statewide 21st Century Skills initiatives.\n\nConditions grant eligibility on a state's: (1) developing a comprehensive plan for such initiative; (2) showing a commitment to advancing such skills within standards and assessments, curriculum, professional development, and the learning environment; (3) achieving broad support for the initiative among state education, business, and civic leaders; and (4) implementing 21st century assessments of education that measure core subjects and 21st century themes, life and career skills, thinking and innovation skills, and information media and technology skills.\n\nDirects the Secretary to establish a 21st Century Skills Incentive Fund from which grants shall be awarded.\n\nAmends the Internal Revenue Code to require that the percentage limitation on corporate charitable contributions be applied separately to cash contributions to state 21st Century Skills initiatives and all other corporate charitable contributions."
  },
